parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Acceleration and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration and loss of control can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the driver may lose control of the vehicle and be unable to stop or steer.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
the vehicle surges forward without input from the driver
the vehicle's speed increases rapidly without warning
the driver loses control of the vehicle
the vehicle is difficult to stop or steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The failure of the braking system to stop the vehicle can further exacerbate the situation.
symptoms: the vehicle surges forward or backward without input from the driver
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle is difficult to control or stops suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic door locks can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to safety issues, such as unintended door opening while driving or difficulty exiting the vehicle in an emergency.
symptoms: The doors lock and unlock randomly
the doors fail to lock or unlock
the door lock switch does not respond.
